# Atlas AI — Cursor commit message generation

When generating a Git commit message for this repository (including Source Control “Generate commit message”), follow these rules exactly.

## Required format (Conventional Commits)

```
<type>(optional-scope): <summary>

[optional body]
```

Rules:

- First line (header) must be ≤ 100 characters
- Use a blank line before any body
- Every body line must be ≤ 100 characters — wrap text; do not emit long single lines
- Subject: imperative mood, no trailing period
- English only
- Prefer a short subject; add a wrapped body only when it clarifies why

## Allowed types

feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore

## Suggested scopes

desktop, core, agents, tools, memory, database, shared, config, docs, scripts

Omit scope when the change is cross-cutting.

## Good examples

```
feat(desktop): add Atlas shell greet IPC bridge

fix(config): resolve print script dist import path

docs: reorganize documentation structure

Move guides and product plans into dedicated folders, add docs hub
indexes, and introduce ADR template plus initial decision records.
```

## Do not

- Write non-conventional messages (e.g. "Update files", "Fixed bug")
- Exceed 100 characters on any line
- Include secrets, API keys, or `.env` contents
- Use Markdown emphasis or emoji in the subject

Project references: `docs/guides/Code-Quality-Standards.md`, `commitlint.config.js`
